=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_T2K_ex1 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_dark mixed sound, with complex oscillator character around 800 Hz, featuring very_slow attack and percussive envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with steep_rolloff character, and spectrally simple.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: very_slow
  brightness: very_dark
  crest_factor_db: percussive
  envelope_flatness: very_dynamic
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: mixed
  spectral_complexity_mean: simple
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 800.0000
  harmonic_decay_rate: -4.2215
  harmonic_regularity: 0.5498
  pitch_clarity: 4.8209
  inharmonicity: 0.0115
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -2.4492
  resonance_freq: 0.0000

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: T2K Example 1
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/T2K.html
// Tags: T2K, Classes
// ---
// --- Example 1 ---
// this does not work:
(
{
    var trig = Dust.ar(4);
    Trig.kr(trig, 0.1) * SinOsc.ar(800) * 0.1
}.play;
)

// this works:
(
{
    var trig = T2K.kr(Dust.ar(4));
    Trig.kr(trig, 0.1) * SinOsc.ar(800) * 0.1
}.play;
)
